magpie.attributes.selectors

Class BaseAttributeSelector

  • java.lang.Object
    • magpie.attributes.selectors.BaseAttributeSelector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, Commandable, Options, Printable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BestIndividualSelector, RegexAttributeSelector, UserSpecifiedAttributeSelector, WekaAttributeSelector

    public abstract class BaseAttributeSelector
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, Options, Printable, Commandable
    Interface to select a subset of attributes for a dataset. Implementations must define a method to select a subset of attribute:

    • train_protected(magpie.data.Dataset) - Select attributes, return list of their indexes
    • Options.setOptions(java.util.List) - Set any options for your implementation. Make sure to make them settable from the Java interface as well.

    Implemented Commands:

    train $<dataset> - Train an attribute selector. Selects a subset of attributes.
    dataset: Dataset used to train selector

    run $<dataset> - Reduce number of attributes in a dataset
    dataset: Dataset to run selector on

      • printDescription

        public java.lang.String printDescription(boolean htmlFormat)
        Description copied from interface: Printable
        Print full name of object, and a simple description of the options. This description should print enough information to reproduce how this object was created, but not necessarily enough to run it (e.g., coefficients for the model).

        Example: For a model training a separate WekaRegression for intermetallics

        magpie.models.regression.SplitRegression

        Splitter: AllMetalsSplitter
        All Metals: magpie.models.regression.WekaRegression trees.REPTree
        Contains Nonmetal: magpie.regression.LASSORegreession -maxterms 2
